The discovery of a strange bacterium that can use the arsenic as one of its nutrients broadens the possibility of finding new forms of life on Earth and possibly on other planets.
Although researchers discovered the curious bacterium here on Earth, they say it demonstrates that there may be life forms without the main elements they considered essential.
"This body has a dual capacity."
"It can grow with either phosphorus or arsenic."
