Avengeant hackers and diligent spies
The WikiLeaks issue has a double value.
On the one hand, it reveals an apparent scandal, a scandal that only seems scandalous to the hypocrisy that governs relations between States, citizens and the press.
On the other hand, it announces profound changes at international level and foresees a future dominated by regression.
But let's go step by step.
The first aspect of WikiLeaks is confirmation of the fact that each file created by a secret service (independently from the nation to which it belongs) consists exclusively of press clippings.
