This is not only because the authors of occult texts do not want to do unpublished research (or do not know where to look for new facts about the non-existent), but because those who dedicate themselves to the occult not only trust what they already know, which confirms what they have already learned.
This is the mechanism for Dan Brown's success.
The same applies to secret files.
The informer is lazy, just as he is lazy (or has little anxiety) the head of the secret services (if he could not be, I know, editor of the Liberation), who only considers true what he can recognize.
The top secret information about Berlusconi that sent the U.S. embassy from Rome to the State Department was the same as the newsweek published the previous week.
Why, then, have the revelations of these records caused such a revolt?
On the one hand, they only say what every cultivated person already knows, that the embassies, at least since World War II and since the Heads of States can call on the telephone or catch the plane to meet for dinner, have lost their diplomatic role and, with the exception of a few limited representation exercises, have become spy centres.
Any viewer who sees research films knows perfectly well, we just seem to know that we don't know it out of hypocrisy.
In any case, repeating it publicly violates the duty of hypocrisy and gives a bad image of American diplomacy.
Secondly, the idea that anyone who hacks can consult the most secret secrets of the most powerful country in the world significantly affects the prestige of the State Department.
The scandal therefore affects both the victims and the "verdugues".
But we enter the true nature of what has happened.
Previously, in Orwell's time, he could conceive of all power as a Big Brother who controlled every gesture of his subjects.
Orwell's prophecy has come true since, being able to control each movement thanks to the telephone, every transaction performed, hotel visited, highway taken, the citizen thus became a complete victim of the eye of power.
But when it is demonstrated, as now happens, that not even the crypts of the secrets of power cannot escape the control of a hacker, the control relationship ceases to be one-way and becomes circular.
Power controls every citizen, but every citizen (at least the hacker, elected as the avenger of citizens) can know all the secrets of power.
How can a power that can no longer even keep its own secrets be endured?
It is true, as Georg Simmel already said, that a true secret is an empty secret (and an empty secret can never be revealed); it is also true that any knowledge about the character of Berlusconi or Merkel is actually an empty secret, without secret, since it comes from the public domain; but to reveal, as WikiLeaks has done, that the secrets of Hillary Clinton were empty secrets means to take away all power from him.
