But it is also clear that, with current technologies, confidential telephone conversations cannot be expected.
Nothing is easier than finding out if and when a Head of State has moved on a plane and has contacted one of the counterparts.
How can they maintain private and confidential relations in the future?
I know perfectly well that for the time being, my forecast is science fiction and, therefore, novice, but I imagine government agents who move discreetly in diligence with uncontrollable itineraries, carrying messages that have been learned from memory or, as much, hiding some data written in the heels of their shoes.
